<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">I wonder too if there was more of this before Agile. With deadline driven development you can run into situations where part of the team is stuck waiting for their teammates to finish something so they can surpass a milestone. You can only poke at the backlog so much. Boredom and being able to rationalize that you aren&#x27;t really affecting the roadmap by sneaking a little extra something in makes for a lot more &#x27;motive and opportunity&#x27; situations.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368971&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44365806%2344368971" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
