<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">Not that I don&#x27;t also wish for a return of more whimsy to software development, but those risks are real— there have been some pretty high profile embarrassments over the years in connection with pranks and easter eggs. The GMail &quot;mic drop&quot; is an obvious one, also the Spider-Man PS4 proposal was another, plus of course stuff like the GTA Hot Coffee minigame.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44369424&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44365806%2344369424" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
