<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">A consequence of drawing the risk line that far to one end is that products end up having no soul. Perfectly valid for a business to decide that.  But it just connects back to my main post and how 80s&#x2F;90s apple had that vibe that today&#x27;s apple lacks. They Risk Managed and&#x2F;or Product Designed until they had a sterile, lifeless product.<p>I think it&#x27;s what I pick up on when I feel annoyed at the emulated soul they try to instil with their design&#x2F;branding&#x2F;commercials.<p>I think another example, sibling to easter eggs, would be April Fools.  Mind you I hate April Fools, but the soul was sterilized as they Risk Managed their way to jokes&#x2F;pranks that were guaranteed to be safe.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44370048&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44365806%2344370048" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
