<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">A lot of the size of the modern operating systems comes from two things:<p>- modern screens are higher resolution, and so require much larger image resources.<p>- modern OSes contain all translations in them. In the 90s it was common to have language-specific versions that only contain that language and maybe English.<p>In the specific case of macOS, it also contains double the code it needs because it runs on both x86 and ARM.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44367009&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44365806%2344367009" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
